 ICS 156: Networking Lab 

   Frame Fields 2/2 
  
     n    Length field    used by 802.3
 standard, packet type     field used by Ethernet, indicates whether network     layer is IP,
 IPX, AppleTalk, etc. In 802.3 the type     field is included in the LLC header.   
     n    Data field    can be
 anywhere from 0 to 1500 bytes.    
     n    PAD field    used by MAC
 to make ensure that     minimum frame length is 64 bytes. (when data     =0bytes, pad
 =46 or 38 bytes)   
  
 

